<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Houston Climate</h2>
<p>For Houston's hot-humid climate, high-efficiency air conditioning systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are recommended to handle the extended cooling season effectively. Two-stage or variable-speed compressors work exceptionally well in Houston because they can run longer at lower speeds, providing better humidity control while maintaining consistent temperatures. Since heating needs are minimal‚Äîtypically required only 60-90 days per year‚Äîa heat pump system often provides the best year-round efficiency, offering 200-400% efficiency compared to electric resistance heating. Gas furnaces paired with high-SEER AC units are also popular, though natural gas availability varies by neighborhood. The key is proper sizing; oversized units short-cycle and fail to remove humidity effectively, while undersized units struggle during Houston's brutal summer peaks when temperatures can reach 105¬∞F with heat indexes above 110¬∞F.</p>

